g-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/women-and-work-scaled.jpeg" data-orig-size="2560,1724" data-comments-opened="0" data-image-meta="{&quot;aperture&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;credit&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;camera&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;caption&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;created_timestamp&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;copyright&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;focal_length&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;iso&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;shutter_speed&quot;:&quot;0&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;&quot;,&quot;orientation&quot;:&quot;1&quot;}" data-image-title="women and work" data-image-description="" data-image-caption="" data-medium-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/women-and-work-750x505.jpeg" data-large-file="https://flowingdata.com/wp-content/uploads/2023/10/women-and-work-1090x734.jpeg" /></a></p><p>哈佛大学经济学家克劳迪娅·戈尔丁 (Claudia Goldin)<a href="https://www.nobelprize.org/prizes/economic-sciences/2023/press-release/">荣获诺贝尔经济学奖</a>。她的研究很大一部分植根于对数百年历史数据的收集和分析：</p><blockquote><p>女性在全球劳动力市场中的代表性严重不足，而且当她们工作时，她们的收入低于男性。克劳迪娅·戈尔丁 (Claudia Goldin) 查阅了档案并收集了美国 200 多年的数据，这使她能够证明收入和就业率方面的性别差异如何以及为何随着时间的推移而发生变化。</p><p>戈尔丁表明，女性劳动力市场参与率在整个时期内并没有呈现上升趋势，而是形成了 U 形曲线。十九世纪初，随着从农业社会向工业社会的转变，已婚妇女的参与程度有所下降，但随着二十世纪初服务业的发展，已婚妇女的参与程度开始增加。戈尔丁将这种模式解释为结构性变化和关于妇女对家庭责任的社会规范不断演变的结果。</p></blockquote><p>惊人的。</p><p>公告附带的约翰·贾内斯塔德 (Johan Jarnestad) 绘制的插图也非常有用。</p><p><strong>标签：</strong><a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/claudia-goldin/" rel="tag">克劳迪娅·戈尔丁</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/economics-2/" rel="tag">经济学</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/gender/" rel="tag">性别</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/nobel-prize/" rel="tag">诺贝尔奖</a>,<a href="https://flowingdata.com/tag/work/" rel="tag">工作</a></p>]]>;</content:encoded><post-id xmlns="com-wordpress:feed-additions:1"> 72349</post-id></item><item><title>绘制以色列和加沙袭击地图</title><link/>https://flowingdata.com/2023/10/09/mapping-israel-and-gaza-attacks/<dc:creator><![CDATA[Nathan Yau]]></dc:creator><pubDate> Mon,